  <mads:note type="source">Four stages of Greek religion, 1912</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Oxford classical dict. (Sallustius, Saloustios, author of brief
    manual of Neoplatonic piety, probably to be identified with Emperor Julian's friend Saturninus 
    Sallustius Secundus)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Sugli dèi e il mondo, 2000: t.p. (Salustio)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Sull'identificazione dell'autore del Peri theōn kai kosmou: p. 123 
    (b. 4th cent. in Gaul) p. 129 (d. before 379)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Brill's new Pauly online, 8 June 2015 (Salustius, philosopher
    of the imperial era, author of a short treatise On the Gods and the Universe (Περὶ
    θεῶν καὶ κόσμου; identity disputed: may be Flavius Sallustius (praef. praed. in Gaul 361-363; cos. 363) 
    or Saturnius Secundus Salutius (praef. praed Orientis 361-365),the treatus was probably 
    written during the reign of Iulianus, in service of the pagan restoration
    and as a reaction to Christianity)</mads:note>
